"{\"uid\": \"newstatesman.com-culture-2024-07-the-1924-paris-olympics-when-athletes-inspired-art\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Reviewing politicsand culture since 1913 The Fitzwilliam Museum's latest show highlights an era that saw the sporting and artistic worlds converge.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 42, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Fitzwilliam Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\"}, {\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fitzwilliam Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"politicsand culture\", \"from\": 10, \"to\": 29}, {\"ngram\": \"an era\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 95}, {\"ngram\": \"the sporting and artistic worlds\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ByEd Smith Excuses are thin on the ground for failing to visit the Fitzwilliam Museum.\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 237, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 218, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fitzwilliam Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ByEd Smith Excuses\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 168}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 181, \"to\": 191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The University of Cambridge's principal museum is surrounded by buildings belonging to its oldest college, Peterhouse.\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peterhouse_Boys'_School\", \"score\": 0.9999897884207047, \"rank\": 1.0211682356775946e-05, \"text\": \"Peterhouse\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peterhouse_Boys'_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peterhouse_Boys'_School\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cambridge\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"buildings\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 311}, {\"ngram\": \"its oldest college\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, for three years, when I was an undergraduate there, it was impossible for me to go very far without walking past it.\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three years\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 376}, {\"ngram\": \"an undergraduate\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet - how do I say this?\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- somehow I never quite made it through the front door.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 563, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the front door\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not once.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thousands of near misses; no hits.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 608, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thousands\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 583}, {\"ngram\": \"near misses\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"no hits\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nor can I blame being late to art - my mother was an art teacher.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"my mother\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"an art teacher\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No, it's even worse than philistinism.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 713, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"philistinism\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of pretentious undergraduate arguments about art and life: many.\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 789, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The number\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 724}, {\"ngram\": \"pretentious undergraduate arguments\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of visits to the actual art gallery: zero.\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 843, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The number\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 800}, {\"ngram\": \"visits\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual art gallery\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 836}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And now, 29 years late, it is sport that draws me across the threshold.\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 916, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 880}, {\"ngram\": \"the threshold\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 915}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To mark the centenary of the 1924 Paris Olympics Games, the Fitzwilliam is staging \\\"Paris 1924: Sport, Art and the Body\\\".\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.126365397775035e-15, \"text\": \"Fitzwilliam\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitzwilliam_Museum\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the centenary\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 938}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1924 Paris Olympics Games\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1006}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"Art\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1023}, {\"ngram\": \"the Body\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a superb show: do visit if you can.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1079, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a superb show\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one sense, the exhibition is tied to Cambridge.\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9990234328039431, \"rank\": 0.0009775218117101918, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one sense\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"the exhibition\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 1924 was theChariots of FireOlympics when the recent graduate Harold Abrahams won gold in the 100-metre dash.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harold Abrahams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"FireOlympics\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1224}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100-metre dash\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1246}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elite universities were bound up with sport's sharp end as well as its nostalgic glow.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Elite universities\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"sport's sharp end\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"its nostalgic glow\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In typically British style, different traditions - a gentlemanly tone but a scientific edge - were being rewritten to meet the needs of the moment.\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8665454074858857, \"rank\": 0.152401502624145, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"different traditions\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1383}, {\"ngram\": \"a gentlemanly tone\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"a scientific edge\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"the needs\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At a deeper level, the exhibition, which features Pablo Picasso, Robert Delaunay and Andr\\u00e9 Lhote among others, is universal.\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1534, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pablo_Picasso\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8143820389644593e-60, \"text\": \"Pablo Picasso\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pablo_Picasso\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pablo_Picasso\"}, {\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Delaunay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Robert Delaunay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Delaunay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Delaunay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a deeper level\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1501}, {\"ngram\": \"the exhibition\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"Andr\\u00e9 Lhote\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In demonstrating the interrelatedness of sport and art in 1924, the show captures a particular cultural moment.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1720, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the interrelatedness\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1646}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1655}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1681}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular cultural moment\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport had suddenly caught artists' attention, especially the cubists and the futurists, and the culture of games and competition looked like the future of art, not just the future of entertainment.\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1726}, {\"ngram\": \"artists' attention\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1765}, {\"ngram\": \"especially the cubists\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"the futurists\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"the culture\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"games\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"not just the future\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"entertainment\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1917}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For that reason, the era under review in Paris 1924 feels like a high watermark.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999992173798, \"rank\": 7.826066394561005e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 1924\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that reason\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1937}, {\"ngram\": \"the era\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"review\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"a high watermark\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because if we step back for a moment and take a wider sweep, sport has ended up with a curious and underdeveloped relationship with painting.\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2039}, {\"ngram\": \"a wider sweep\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2062}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"a curious and underdeveloped relationship\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2129}, {\"ngram\": \"painting\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2143}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why did the tradition not quite develop?\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2185, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tradition\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How come sport and art looked set to have a much more interesting future together than the one that transpired?\", \"from\": 2186, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"a much more interesting future\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"the one\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Partly, of course, sports painting was superseded by sports photography.\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2371, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"sports painting\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2333}, {\"ngram\": \"sports photography\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today's athletes are among the most photographed people in the world.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2441, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Today's athletes\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"the most photographed people\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2427}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American sportswriter George Plimpton deftly summarised the problem of \\\"painting sport\\\" in his assessment of a 1920s realist boxing canvas by George Bellows.\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2446, \"end\": 2454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999961021861531, \"rank\": 3.003376536290844e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2468, \"end\": 2483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Plimpton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"George Plimpton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Plimpton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Plimpton\"}, {\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Bellows\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"George Bellows\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Bellows\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Bellows\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the problem\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2513}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2532}, {\"ngram\": \"his assessment\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2551}, {\"ngram\": \"a 1920s realist boxing canvas\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the kind of painting, Plimpton quipped, \\\"that photography really does now\\\".\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2686, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2619}, {\"ngram\": \"painting\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2631}, {\"ngram\": \"Plimpton\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2641}, {\"ngram\": \"that photography\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2668}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Exactly.\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How does a painter find a unique perspective when sport is broadcast in high definition and photographed from every angle?\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2818, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a painter\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2714}, {\"ngram\": \"a unique perspective\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2746, \"to\": 2751}, {\"ngram\": \"high definition\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2783}, {\"ngram\": \"every angle\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is more to the difficulty of \\\"sports art\\\" than just the ubiquity of mainstream photography.\", \"from\": 2820, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the difficulty\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2855}, {\"ngram\": \"sports art\", \"from\": 2860, \"to\": 2870}, {\"ngram\": \"just the ubiquity\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2894}, {\"ngram\": \"mainstream photography\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think there is something more fundamental.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2948}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, although my own sport - cricket - has inspired some celebrated paintings, almost all of them succeed by evoking the aesthetic backdrop, the ambience or the social scene; none springs to mind that takes us into the heat of the competitive story.\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 3224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"my own sport - cricket\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"some celebrated paintings\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"almost all\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3064}, {\"ngram\": \"the aesthetic backdrop\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3114}, {\"ngram\": \"the ambience\", \"from\": 3116, \"to\": 3128}, {\"ngram\": \"the social scene\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3148}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3154}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3184}, {\"ngram\": \"the heat\", \"from\": 3190, \"to\": 3198}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitive story\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport, having already created its own dramatic world, generally resists a second layer of (artistic) dramatisation.\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3340, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3230}, {\"ngram\": \"its own dramatic world\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3277}, {\"ngram\": \"a second layer\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3311}, {\"ngram\": \"(artistic) dramatisation\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In some respects, the athlete and the artist - as rival creators of stories about the human condition - are trespassing on each other's territory.\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3487, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some respects\", \"from\": 3344, \"to\": 3357}, {\"ngram\": \"the athlete\", \"from\": 3359, \"to\": 3370}, {\"ngram\": \"the artist\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3385}, {\"ngram\": \"rival creators\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3405}, {\"ngram\": \"stories\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"the human condition\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3442}, {\"ngram\": \"each other's territory\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Which is why I think sports painting may be best suited to partial abstraction.\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3568, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports painting\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3525}, {\"ngram\": \"partial abstraction\", \"from\": 3548, \"to\": 3567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's often the case with the standouts in this exhibition.\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3633, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 3586, \"to\": 3594}, {\"ngram\": \"the standouts\", \"from\": 3600, \"to\": 3613}, {\"ngram\": \"this exhibition\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andr\\u00e9 Lhote'sTennis Playerssplices tennis rackets and stylised bob-haired players - but we still know exactly what they are doing, that it's cool, and that sport feels like the future.\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andr\\u00e9_Lhote\", \"score\": 0.9969615836180966, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lhote\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andr\\u00e9_Lhote\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andr\\u00e9_Lhote\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"stylised bob-haired players\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3715}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 3736, \"to\": 3748}, {\"ngram\": \"that sport\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3795}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 3807, \"to\": 3817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Robert Delaunay'sRunners, inspired by the 1924 Paris Games, we see five runners taking a bend on the track together.\", \"from\": 3820, \"to\": 3939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3823, \"end\": 3838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Delaunay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Robert Delaunay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Delaunay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Delaunay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1924 Paris Games\", \"from\": 3861, \"to\": 3881}, {\"ngram\": \"five runners\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 3902}, {\"ngram\": \"a bend\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 3916}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 3929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the real focus and energy of the painting does not derive from the humans (who are not given faces, let alone expressions), but from their colourful and contrasting athletic strips.\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 4125, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the real focus\", \"from\": 3944, \"to\": 3958}, {\"ngram\": \"energy\", \"from\": 3963, \"to\": 3969}, {\"ngram\": \"the painting\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 3985}, {\"ngram\": \"the humans\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4017}, {\"ngram\": \"faces\", \"from\": 4037, \"to\": 4042}, {\"ngram\": \"expressions\", \"from\": 4054, \"to\": 4065}, {\"ngram\": \"their colourful and contrasting athletic strips\", \"from\": 4077, \"to\": 4124}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their colours are competing, in the race and in the painting.\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4187, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their colours\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4139}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 4158, \"to\": 4166}, {\"ngram\": \"the painting\", \"from\": 4174, \"to\": 4186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before seeing it in person, I had not understood how Delaunay'sRunnerscaptures sport not just with colour, but also illuminates sport through colour.\", \"from\": 4188, \"to\": 4337, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4214}, {\"ngram\": \"colour\", \"from\": 4287, \"to\": 4293}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 4316, \"to\": 4321}, {\"ngram\": \"colour\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another highlight (and similarly partially abstracted) was entirely new to me: Enzo Benedetto'sCyclist.\", \"from\": 4339, \"to\": 4442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another highlight\", \"from\": 4339, \"to\": 4356}, {\"ngram\": \"Enzo Benedetto'sCyclist\", \"from\": 4418, \"to\": 4441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Italian futurists were obsessed by sport and the rise of the machine.\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4447, \"end\": 4464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Futurism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Italian futurists\", \